{
  "name": "shimmerwire",
  "description": "A hammered dulcimer cascading bright struck-wire shimmer, like rain on a tin sunroof at noon. Rapid struck-wire dulcimer tones, bright and ringing with overlapping metallic decay; cascading and shimmering, folk-bright and tumbling, pure daylit sparkle. A low warm bass-course is the cascade floor; a mid hammered course tumbles the melody answered by a quicker, brighter counter-line; a soft-hammered sweet middle rings warm; a high single-wire ping glints; rapid top-course hammer-rolls cascade bright droplets with delay echoes; a tremolo-roll bloom and a churning shimmer-cloud swell across courses; a damped frame-tap keeps the pulse and a bright top-course flick sparkles the accents. A major pentatonic @ A=432, additive and clean, hall reverb, never dreary.",
  "drone": null,
  "master_gain": 0.45,
  "drone_gain": 0.0,
  "reverb_scale": 1.0,
